    "title": "Lentil and bacon soup",
    "subtitle": "Smoky, thick, and satisfying",
    "excerpt": "Red lentils simmered with smoked bacon lardons, carrots, and celery into a thick, hearty soup. One of the most inexpensive and filling meals in the repertoire. Ready in 40 minutes.",
    "sourceNotes": "A standard of British home cooking, widely published in post-war cookery books. The combination of smoked bacon and lentils draws on French and British traditions of using cured pork to flavour pulses.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Lentil and bacon soup is one of the most dependable weekday meals: cheap, filling, and better after a night in the fridge. The red lentils dissolve into the broth without any soaking or blending, which means the only thing that needs attention is the initial frying of the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "lardons",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                  "attrs": {
                    "termId": "cmpry23a20000nkv41lhwldoh"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " and vegetables. Everything else takes care of itself.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
