        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Fry the bacon and vegetables",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat a large saucepan over a medium heat. Add the {{lardons}} of smoked lardons and fry for 5 minutes until golden and the fat has rendered. Spoon out a few tablespoons to garnish later.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{onion}} onion, {{carrot}} carrots, and {{celery}} celery to the pan. Cook in the bacon fat for 8 minutes until softened. Add the {{garlic}} of garlic, {{thyme-dried}} of dried thyme, and {{tomato-puree}} of tomato purée. Cook for 1 minute.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Add lentils and simmer",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add {{lentils-red}} of rinsed red lentils and pour over {{stock-chicken}} of hot stock. Bring to a simmer, cover, and cook for 25 minutes until the lentils have dissolved into the soup.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Taste and season. The bacon provides a lot of salt; add cautiously.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle into bowls. Scatter the reserved crispy lardons over the top and add a handful of flat-leaf parsley if using.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Add hot water or stock 100 ml at a time and stir. Red lentil soups routinely need thinning on reheating.",
                "cause": "Red lentils thicken considerably as they dissolve.",
                "symptom": "Soup is too thick"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use low-salt or homemade stock. Taste before seasoning and add salt only at the very end.",
                "cause": "Smoked lardons are salty, and some stocks are too.",
                "symptom": "Soup is too salty"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Buy lentils from a shop with high turnover. Increase the simmer slightly and cook for another 10 minutes. Older lentils can take up to 40 minutes.",
                "cause": "Very old lentils, or the simmer was too gentle.",
                "symptom": "Lentils are still grainy after 25 minutes"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Fry the reserved lardons separately in a dry non-stick pan over a high heat for 3 to 4 minutes until properly crisp before adding to the bowl.",
                "cause": "Too much fat in the pan or bacon was added before the pan was hot.",
                "symptom": "Bacon is not crispy enough as a garnish"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Smoked pork with pulses is a combination found from the French cassoulet tradition through to British pea soup with ham hock. Lentil and bacon soup sits in the middle of that tradition: not as formal as a French lentilles du Puy or as long-cooked as a ham hock soup, but a reliable weekday version that most households have a version of. The red lentil, which dissolves without soaking or blending, makes it one of the easiest thick soups to cook.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
